  "text": "Construct validities are concerned with the extent to which the objects of study truly represents theory behind the study [CITATION_1] . We collected data from different sources (e.g, different countries, industrial sectors, etc.) in order to avoid monooperation bias. It is also common for people to deflect their answers when they feel being evaluated and based on what they think is the intended result of a study. To mitigate these, we informed participants prior to the survey that our motive in this study was to take a snapshot of the industry and that we will not collect any identifying information so that participants will remain anonymous.",
